    "body": "<p>There is a baby monkey in Monkey Kingdom, who is so mischievous. His instructor wants him to learn\nto climb a rope.But when instructor instructs him to climb a rope of length L meter.He always\nclimbs up M meters and slips down N meters.And he takes 1 min for each meter up and down.\nNow help the instructor to find the total time(in minutes) taken by the baby monkey to reach at the \nend of rope.\nPrint -1 if he can not reaches at the end of the rope.</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>First line contains T test cases.\nNext T lines contains L, M & N.<br>\nWhere L meters is the height of rope, M is the height in meters climbed up by monkey and N is the height in meters monkey slipped down.</p>\n\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>There are T number of output lines containing the total time taken by the baby monkey to reach at \nthe end of the rope.\n</p>\n\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>99</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>L</b> \u2264 <b>999</b></li>\n<li><b>0</b> \u2264 <b>M</b> \u2264 <b>L</b></li>\n<li><b>0</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>L</b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n4\n10 5 2\n20 10 10\n30 15 5\n40 10 20\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n18\n-1\n50\n-1\n</pre>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p>In first attempt he will climb 5 meters taking 5 seconds and will slip 2 meters taking 2 second. Now he is 3 meters from ground.\nThen he will climb 5 meters taking 5 seconds and will slip 2 meters taking 2 seconds. Now he is 6 meters from ground.\nAfter that he will 4 meter and will reach at the end of the rope.\nSo total time is 5+2+5+2+4=18.</p>",
